cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with multiple object tracking and appearance models in 3D space, which are core topics in computer vision.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the proposed method can be applied to robotics applications such as autonomous driving and drone navigation.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes an adaptive appearance model that learns online, which involves machine learning techniques.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with intelligent tracking of multiple objects in 3D space, which is a subfield of AI.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the least likely category as the paper does not deal with cryptography or security.
